<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880909-0004 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Computer Sciences Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CSC </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Computer Sciences Corp. said it agreed to acquire closely held Index Group Inc., a Cambridge, Mass., management consulting firm.    Terms weren't disclosed. Index employs 140 people in offices in Cambridge, Los Angeles and London, and has annual revenue of about $30 million. In addition to consulting, the firm conducts management-education programs and corporate-sponsored research for nearly 200 large companies, Computer Sciences said.    William R. Hoover, chairman and president of Computer Sciences, an El Segundo, Calif., computer-services concern, said the proposed acquisition &quot;adds senior consulting leadership in the strategic use of information resources to our extensive capabilities in system design and implementation.&quot;    Separately, Computer Sciences said it completed the sale of 40% of its Infonet unit and granted options to buy an additional 15% of the unit to telecommunications authorities for several foreign countries. Infonet sells data communications services. </TEXT></DOC>